.Dd $Mdocdate: June 28 2026 $
.Dt SLAC.TOML 5
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm slac.toml
.Nd spam classifier delivery agent configuration file
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
is the configuration file for
.Xr slac 8 .
The file uses TOML syntax and is divided into tables for classifier,
delivery, quarantine, and review feedback behavior.
.Pp
When no explicit file is given with
.Fl c ,
.Xr slac 8
searches:
.Pp
.Bl -enum -compact
.It
.Pa ~/.config/slac/slac.toml
.It
.Pa /etc/slac.toml
.El
.Pp
If neither file exists,
built-in defaults are used.
In MDA mode, read or parse errors are logged and delivery falls back to the
built-in defaults.
Review commands report configuration errors directly.
.Sh TABLES
.Ss llm
The
.Ic llm
table configures the OpenAI-compatible chat completions endpoint.
.Bl -tag -width json_response_format
.It Ic endpoint
HTTP URL for the chat completions endpoint.
The default is
.Pa http://127.0.0.1:8080/v1/chat/completions .
.It Ic api_key
Optional bearer token used for the
.Ql Authorization
header.
No API key is sent by default.
.It Ic model
Model name sent in the chat completion request.
The default is
.Dq local-model .
.It Ic temperature
Sampling temperature sent in the request.
The default is
.Dq 0.0 .
.It Ic timeout_seconds
HTTP timeout for classifier requests.
The default is
.Dq 30 .
.It Ic json_response_format
When true,
request
.Dq json_object
response format from the endpoint.
Some local OpenAI-compatible servers do not support this field.
The default is true.
.El
.Ss classification
The
.Ic classification
table controls header insertion, prompt size, and quarantine eligibility.
.Bl -tag -width max_prompt_bytes
.It Ic observe_only
When true,
.Xr slac 8
classifies and annotates messages but always delivers normally.
This should be used while testing a new classifier.
The default is true.
.It Ic add_headers
When true,
add
.Ql X-SLAC-*
classification or classifier-error headers to delivered or quarantined mail.
The default is true.
.It Ic spam_threshold
Minimum classifier spam probability required before quarantine is considered.
The default is
.Dq 0.85 .
.It Ic max_prompt_bytes
Maximum number of message bytes included in the classifier prompt.
The default is
.Dq 49152 .
.It Ic max_body_bytes
Maximum number of message body bytes included in the classifier prompt.
The default is
.Dq 32768 .
.El
.Ss delivery
The
.Ic delivery
table configures normal local delivery.
.Bl -tag -width command
.It Ic command
Program executed for normal delivery.
The message is written to the program's standard input.
The default is
.Pa /usr/libexec/mail.local .
.It Ic args
Array of arguments passed to
.Ic command
after template expansion.
The default is:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
["-f", "{sender}", "{user}"]
.Ed
.El
.Ss quarantine
The
.Ic quarantine
table configures spam storage.
.Bl -tag -width require_verdict
.It Ic path
Path to an mbox used for quarantined messages.
Templates are expanded before use.
The default is
.Pa {home}/spam .
.It Ic require_verdict
Verdict policy required for quarantine after the spam threshold has been met.
Valid values are:
.Pp
.Bl -tag -width spam_or_unsure -compact
.It Cm spam
Only quarantine messages with verdict
.Dq spam .
.It Cm spam_or_unsure
Quarantine messages with verdict
.Dq spam
or
.Dq unsure .
.It Cm any
Quarantine any message whose spam probability meets the threshold,
regardless of verdict.
.El
.Pp
The default is
.Cm spam .
.El
.Ss feedback
The
.Ic feedback
table controls use of user correction history in classifier prompts.
.Bl -tag -width max_examples
.It Ic enabled
When true,
recent correction records from
.Pa ~/.local/share/slac/corrections.jsonl
are included in the prompt as bounded examples.
The default is true.
.It Ic max_examples
Maximum number of correction records to include.
The default is
.Dq 20 .
.It Ic max_bytes
Maximum correction-history bytes to include.
The default is
.Dq 8192 .
.El
.Ss rules
.Ic rules
is a top-level array of strings.
Each string is added to the classifier prompt as local policy guidance.
If omitted,
a small built-in rule set is used.
.Sh TEMPLATES
The following template strings are expanded in
.Ic delivery.args
and
.Ic quarantine.path :
.Bl -tag -width "{recipient}" -compact
.It Ic {sender}
The
.Ev SENDER
environment variable.
.It Ic {user}
The
.Ev USER
environment variable, or
.Ev LOGNAME
if
.Ev USER
is unset.
.It Ic {recipient}
The
.Ev RECIPIENT
environment variable.
.It Ic {home}
The
.Ev HOME
environment variable.
.El
.Pp
Unknown template strings are left unchanged.
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width "~/.local/share/slac/corrections/messages/" -compact
.It Pa /etc/slac.toml
System configuration file.
.It Pa ~/.config/slac/slac.toml
Per-user configuration file.
.It Pa ~/.local/share/slac/corrections.jsonl
Correction history read when feedback is enabled.
.It Pa ~/.local/share/slac/corrections/messages/
Corrected message snapshots.
.El
.Sh EXAMPLES
A conservative initial configuration that annotates mail but never
quarantines:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
[llm]
endpoint = "http://127.0.0.1:8080/v1/chat/completions"
model = "local-model"
temperature = 0.0
timeout_seconds = 30
json_response_format = true

[classification]
observe_only = true
add_headers = true
spam_threshold = 0.95
max_prompt_bytes = 49152
max_body_bytes = 32768

[delivery]
command = "/usr/libexec/mail.local"
args = ["-f", "{sender}", "{user}"]

[quarantine]
path = "{home}/spam"
require_verdict = "spam"

[feedback]
enabled = true
max_examples = 20
max_bytes = 8192

rules = [
  "Credential harvesting is a strong spam or phishing signal.",
  "Legitimate transactional mail has clear sender identity.",
]
.Ed
.Pp
After observing classifier behavior, enable quarantine:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
[classification]
observe_only = false
add_headers = true
spam_threshold = 0.95

[quarantine]
path = "{home}/spam"
require_verdict = "spam"
.Ed
.Pp
Disable
.Ic json_response_format
for an endpoint that rejects the OpenAI response format field:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
[llm]
endpoint = "http://127.0.0.1:8080/v1/chat/completions"
model = "local-model"
json_response_format = false
.Ed
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr smtpd.conf 5 ,
.Xr mail.local 8 ,
.Xr slac 8 ,
.Xr smtpd 8
